{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778975269196,"sessionID":"ses_1ccd7b077ffeG5neEOCLcs0A6b","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_t6sVH61KJHt2P74UFVOxFU9B","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: RESEARCH.md\n+# Research for GO issue 31863\n+\n+## PMID:19887069 \"Role of vesicle tethering factors in the ER-Golgi membrane traffic\"\n+\n+Sztul and Lupashin review vesicle tethering factors in ER-Golgi traffic. The abstract supports the requested definition by describing tethering factors as mediating the initial attachment of transport carriers to acceptor membranes prior to fusion, and as static bridges that contribute to selectivity in vesicle fusion.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:19887069 \"A well-accepted role for tethering factors is the initial attachment of transport carriers to acceptor membranes prior to fusion.\"\n+\n+## PMID:19575650 \"Tethering factors as organizers of intracellular vesicular traffic\"\n+\n+Yu and Hughson provide a broader review of vesicle tethering in intracellular trafficking. The abstract supports the general molecular-function term because it discusses budding, transport, tethering and fusion of transport vesicles, and describes tethering factors as large complexes involved in intracellular trafficking pathways that interact with other trafficking machinery.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:19575650 \"Intracellular trafficking entails the budding, transport, tethering, and fusion of transport vesicles and other membrane carriers.\"\n*** Add File: DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n+# Design Pattern Review for GO issue 31863\n+\n+## Requested term\n+\n+`vesicle membrane tethering activity` is a molecular function term requested as a child of `GO:0140177 membrane-membrane adaptor activity`.\n+\n+## Pattern assessment\n+\n+No specific DOSDP pattern was found for membrane-membrane adaptor activity or vesicle membrane tethering activity. The generic `binding.yaml` pattern exists, but it would not be appropriate to use here because the requested term is not simply binding to one material entity; it is an adaptor/tether activity that brings two membranes together prior to docking and fusion.\n+\n+## Existing ontology precedent\n+\n+Relevant existing parent and sibling terms:\n+\n+* `GO:0140177 membrane-membrane adaptor activity`: \"The binding activity of a molecule that brings together two membranes, either via membrane lipid binding or by interacting with a membrane protein, to establish or maintain the localization of the protein, protein complex, vesicle or organelle.\"\n+* `GO:0160321 vesicle docking activity`: sibling molecular-function term under `GO:0140177`; its comment explicitly positions docking after vesicle tethering activity and before fusogenic activity.\n+* `GO:0099022 vesicle tethering`: biological-process term defining vesicle tethering as an initial, indirect interaction between a vesicle membrane and a target membrane, distinct from and prior to fusion.\n+* Other children of `GO:0140177`, such as mitochondrion-plasma membrane adaptor activity and peroxisome-mitochondrion membrane tether activity, use asserted `is_a: GO:0140177` without logical definitions.\n+\n+## Decision\n+\n+The existing `GO:7770062 vesicle membrane tethering activity` stanza follows the appropriate precedent: asserted `is_a` to `GO:0140177`, no `intersection_of` logical definition, definition references validated PMIDs, term tracker link to issue 31863, and creation metadata because it is a new term.\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA RESEARCH.md\nA DESIGN_PATTERNS.md","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,13 @@\n+# Research for GO issue 31863\n+\n+## PMID:19887069 \"Role of vesicle tethering factors in the ER-Golgi membrane traffic\"\n+\n+Sztul and Lupashin review vesicle tethering factors in ER-Golgi traffic. The abstract supports the requested definition by describing tethering factors as mediating the initial attachment of transport carriers to acceptor membranes prior to fusion, and as static bridges that contribute to selectivity in vesicle fusion.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:19887069 \"A well-accepted role for tethering factors is the initial attachment of transport carriers to acceptor membranes prior to fusion.\"\n+\n+## PMID:19575650 \"Tethering factors as organizers of intracellular vesicular traffic\"\n+\n+Yu and Hughson provide a broader review of vesicle tethering in intracellular trafficking. The abstract supports the general molecular-function term because it discusses budding, transport, tethering and fusion of transport vesicles, and describes tethering factors as large complexes involved in intracellular trafficking pathways that interact with other trafficking machinery.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:19575650 \"Intracellular trafficking entails the budding, transport, tethering, and fusion of transport vesicles and other membrane carriers.\"\n\nIndex: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,22 @@\n+# Design Pattern Review for GO issue 31863\n+\n+## Requested term\n+\n+`vesicle membrane tethering activity` is a molecular function term requested as a child of `GO:0140177 membrane-membrane adaptor activity`.\n+\n+## Pattern assessment\n+\n+No specific DOSDP pattern was found for membrane-membrane adaptor activity or vesicle membrane tethering activity. The generic `binding.yaml` pattern exists, but it would not be appropriate to use here because the requested term is not simply binding to one material entity; it is an adaptor/tether activity that brings two membranes together prior to docking and fusion.\n+\n+## Existing ontology precedent\n+\n+Relevant existing parent and sibling terms:\n+\n+* `GO:0140177 membrane-membrane adaptor activity`: \"The binding activity of a molecule that brings together two membranes, either via membrane lipid binding or by interacting with a membrane protein, to establish or maintain the localization of the protein, protein complex, vesicle or organelle.\"\n+* `GO:0160321 vesicle docking activity`: sibling molecular-function term under `GO:0140177`; its comment explicitly positions docking after vesicle tethering activity and before fusogenic activity.\n+* `GO:0099022 vesicle tethering`: biological-process term defining vesicle tethering as an initial, indirect interaction between a vesicle membrane and a target membrane, distinct from and prior to fusion.\n+* Other children of `GO:0140177`, such as mitochondrion-plasma membrane adaptor activity and peroxisome-mitochondrion membrane tether activity, use asserted `is_a: GO:0140177` without logical definitions.\n+\n+## Decision\n+\n+The existing `GO:7770062 vesicle membrane tethering activity` stanza follows the appropriate precedent: asserted `is_a` to `GO:0140177`, no `intersection_of` logical definition, definition references validated PMIDs, term tracker link to issue 31863, and creation metadata because it is a new term.\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md","relativePath":"RESEARCH.md","type":"add","patch":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,13 @@\n+# Research for GO issue 31863\n+\n+## PMID:19887069 \"Role of vesicle tethering factors in the ER-Golgi membrane traffic\"\n+\n+Sztul and Lupashin review vesicle tethering factors in ER-Golgi traffic. The abstract supports the requested definition by describing tethering factors as mediating the initial attachment of transport carriers to acceptor membranes prior to fusion, and as static bridges that contribute to selectivity in vesicle fusion.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:19887069 \"A well-accepted role for tethering factors is the initial attachment of transport carriers to acceptor membranes prior to fusion.\"\n+\n+## PMID:19575650 \"Tethering factors as organizers of intracellular vesicular traffic\"\n+\n+Yu and Hughson provide a broader review of vesicle tethering in intracellular trafficking. The abstract supports the general molecular-function term because it discusses budding, transport, tethering and fusion of transport vesicles, and describes tethering factors as large complexes involved in intracellular trafficking pathways that interact with other trafficking machinery.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:19575650 \"Intracellular trafficking entails the budding, transport, tethering, and fusion of transport vesicles and other membrane carriers.\"\n","additions":13,"deletions":0},{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md","relativePath":"DESIGN_PATTERNS.md","type":"add","patch":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,22 @@\n+# Design Pattern Review for GO issue 31863\n+\n+## Requested term\n+\n+`vesicle membrane tethering activity` is a molecular function term requested as a child of `GO:0140177 membrane-membrane adaptor activity`.\n+\n+## Pattern assessment\n+\n+No specific DOSDP pattern was found for membrane-membrane adaptor activity or vesicle membrane tethering activity. The generic `binding.yaml` pattern exists, but it would not be appropriate to use here because the requested term is not simply binding to one material entity; it is an adaptor/tether activity that brings two membranes together prior to docking and fusion.\n+\n+## Existing ontology precedent\n+\n+Relevant existing parent and sibling terms:\n+\n+* `GO:0140177 membrane-membrane adaptor activity`: \"The binding activity of a molecule that brings together two membranes, either via membrane lipid binding or by interacting with a membrane protein, to establish or maintain the localization of the protein, protein complex, vesicle or organelle.\"\n+* `GO:0160321 vesicle docking activity`: sibling molecular-function term under `GO:0140177`; its comment explicitly positions docking after vesicle tethering activity and before fusogenic activity.\n+* `GO:0099022 vesicle tethering`: biological-process term defining vesicle tethering as an initial, indirect interaction between a vesicle membrane and a target membrane, distinct from and prior to fusion.\n+* Other children of `GO:0140177`, such as mitochondrion-plasma membrane adaptor activity and peroxisome-mitochondrion membrane tether activity, use asserted `is_a: GO:0140177` without logical definitions.\n+\n+## Decision\n+\n+The existing `GO:7770062 vesicle membrane tethering activity` stanza follows the appropriate precedent: asserted `is_a` to `GO:0140177`, no `intersection_of` logical definition, definition references validated PMIDs, term tracker link to issue 31863, and creation metadata because it is a new term.\n","additions":22,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA RESEARCH.md\nA DESIGN_PATTERNS.md","time":{"start":1778975269177,"end":1778975269193}},"id":"prt_e33302dbe0016y1bFk22ThVmZm","sessionID":"ses_1ccd7b077ffeG5neEOCLcs0A6b","messageID":"msg_e333003ba001CBrAFY64kH4cBq"}}
