{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778975768724,"sessionID":"ses_1ccd7b077ffeG5neEOCLcs0A6b","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_XFNDKpghByyoVlog8cUFTFAT","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+Changes committed in PR #<NN>.\n+\n+The requested `vesicle membrane tethering activity` term is present as `GO:7770062`, with `GO:0140177 membrane-membrane adaptor activity` as its parent. The parent definition already includes vesicle, and I added the issue 31863 tracker link to the parent term so the definition update is explicitly connected to this request.\n+\n+Full ontology validation passed with `make -C src/ontology travis_build`.\n*** Add File: PR_COMMENTS.md\n+# Summary\n+\n+Addressed GO issue 31863 for `vesicle membrane tethering activity`.\n+\n+The local ontology already contained the requested new term:\n+\n+* `GO:7770062 vesicle membrane tethering activity`\n+* Parent: `GO:0140177 membrane-membrane adaptor activity`\n+* Definition references: `PMID:19575650`, `PMID:19887069`\n+* Synonyms: `vesicle membrane tether activity`, `vesicle tethering activity`\n+* Tracker link: `https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31863`\n+\n+The local ontology also already had the requested parent definition update for `GO:0140177`, including \"vesicle\" in the list of localized entities. I added the missing `term_tracker_item` link for issue 31863 to `GO:0140177` so the parent definition update is traceable to this issue.\n+\n+# Rationale\n+\n+`GO:7770062` is appropriately modeled as an asserted child of `GO:0140177`, consistent with sibling membrane tether/adaptor molecular-function terms. No logical definition was added: no specific membrane-membrane adaptor activity design pattern was found, and the generic binding pattern would over-specify the term because this function bridges two membranes rather than simply binding one material entity.\n+\n+The references were validated:\n+\n+* `PMID:19887069` supports vesicle tethering factors as mediating the initial attachment of transport carriers to acceptor membranes prior to fusion.\n+* `PMID:19575650` supports vesicle tethering as part of intracellular trafficking, covering transport vesicles and membrane carriers broadly.\n+\n+# Validation\n+\n+* Pre-validation passed: `make -C src/ontology travis_build`\n+* Reference text validation passed for supporting excerpts in `RESEARCH.md`\n+* Post-change validation passed: `make -C src/ontology travis_build`\n+\n+# Checklist\n+\n+* [x] PLAN: Issue context and comments reviewed; requested term and parent definition update were clear.\n+* [x] PRE-VALIDATION: Current ontology validated before edits.\n+* [x] RESEARCH: `RESEARCH.md` created; PMIDs validated with `linkml-reference-validator`.\n+* [x] TERM-SEARCH: Existing GO terms checked, including `GO:0140177`, `GO:7770062`, `GO:0099022`, `GO:0090522`, `GO:0099041`, and `GO:0160321`.\n+* [x] DESIGN-PATTERNS: `DESIGN_PATTERNS.md` created; no specific pattern found; generic binding pattern rejected as too broad/incorrect for this term.\n+* [x] EDITS: Used `obo-checkout.pl` and `obo-checkin.pl` for the parent term metadata edit.\n+* [x] RELATIONSHIPS: Existing `GO:7770062 is_a GO:0140177` relationship confirmed appropriate; no `intersection_of` added.\n+* [x] SPECIALIZED-EDITS: N/A; no CHEBI, catalytic activity, mapping, taxon constraint, or obsoletion edits.\n+* [x] METADATA: Added issue 31863 tracker link to `GO:0140177`; confirmed `GO:7770062` has required new-term metadata.\n+* [x] AUTOMATED-VALIDATION: Full `travis_build` passed after the change.\n+* [x] REFERENCE-VALIDATION: PMIDs validated and support text checked.\n+* [x] CHANGES-COMMITTED: Committed only `src/ontology/go-edit.obo`.\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\nA PR_COMMENTS.md","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n====================================